Project: traditional-homes.gr
Stack: Astro (static output) + Tailwind CSS + TypeScript. Deploy target: Cloudflare Pages.
Do NOT convert this project to React/Vite/Next. Do NOT add React dependencies. No lucide-react.

Rules (non-negotiable):
1) Minimal diffs: change only what the request requires. Do not refactor unrelated files.
2) Do not install new npm packages unless strictly required. If required, explain why and keep it to one package.
3) Use existing components and styles. Keep the design calm and consistent (no “template-y” UI).
4) SEO must be correct:
   - Every page must set unique: title + meta description + canonical.
   - Keep OpenGraph + Twitter meta.
   - Add JSON-LD where relevant (Organization site-wide; LodgingBusiness/Hotel on unit pages).
   - No keyword stuffing. Use factual copy.
   - Ensure headings are hierarchical (one H1 per page), images have descriptive alt text.
5) Data rules:
   - inventory.json is the source of truth. Do not change its schema unless explicitly asked.
   - Adapt templates/components to read from inventory.json as-is.
6) Cloudflare-ready:
   - Static only. No server runtime assumptions.
   - Support public/robots.txt, public/_headers, and sitemap output.

Work style:
- Before coding, summarize your plan in 3–6 bullets and list the exact files you will edit.
- Then implement.
